Description: Fragment of foot and stem of South Ionian pottery cup, presumably a cup with everted rim; broad resting surface and hollow stem; exterior glazed black; underside reserved; inscription on underside.
Type series: Vallet and Villard Ionian Cup Type B2
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 372)
Schlotzhauer 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus Naukratis (p. 54, no. 10)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.511) (Phase 3)
